channel.title: SkyLearn Pre-Filter Test Feed – New Batch v2
channel.description: Ten brand-new mixed articles for keyword filter testing

item.title: JLL moves UK head office to new smart workspace near Liverpool Street
item.description: JLL has relocated its UK headquarters to 1 Broadgate, adopting an open-plan smart office designed for hybrid working.

item.title: Adele releases new single ahead of world tour announcement
item.description: The singer surprised fans with an emotional ballad premiered live on BBC Radio 2.

item.title: Aviva Investors signs pre-let deal for 120,000 sq ft at King’s Cross
item.description: The insurer has agreed a long-term lease for a new energy-efficient headquarters at the Arbour scheme.

item.title: Strictly Come Dancing final set for Wembley Arena special
item.description: The BBC confirmed this year’s grand final will take place in front of 12,000 fans for the first time.

item.title: Deutsche Bank consolidates London footprint with move to Broadgate
item.description: The bank will relocate staff from three separate offices into a single 400,000 sq ft hub by late 2026.

item.title: Lewis Hamilton opens new vegan restaurant in Shoreditch
item.description: The Formula 1 champion’s eatery focuses on plant-based comfort food and sustainable design.

item.title: Canary Wharf Group launches new co-working campus aimed at tech startups
item.description: The 200,000 sq ft flexible workspace will attract scale-ups relocating from West London and the South Bank.

item.title: Eurovision 2026 host city revealed as Glasgow
item.description: Organisers confirmed Glasgow will host next year’s contest, with ticket sales opening in January.

item.title: Siemens opens regional innovation centre in Cambridge Science Park
item.description: Siemens has opened a new R&D hub to accommodate 600 staff relocating from multiple UK satellite offices.

item.title: Rihanna launches luxury fashion collaboration with Burberry
item.description: The capsule collection merges high fashion with streetwear influences, set to drop worldwide next month.
